@startuml DailyProblemClassification_SP_InsertProbation
title CTS_DC_CustClassification_ProblemAccountProbation_Insert - Detailed Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E1F5FE
skinparam activityBorderColor #0277BD

start

:Stored Procedure Called;
note right
  **SP Name**: CTS_DC_CustClassification_ProblemAccountProbation_Insert
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsServiceAdmin (MySQL)
  **Timeout**: 300 seconds (default)
  **Parameters**: @ip_ProblemAccount (JSON)
  **Called From**: ProblemAccountProbationInsertCriteria
end note

:Receive JSON Input;
note right
  **Input Parameter**: @ip_ProblemAccount (JSON string)
  
  **JSON Structure**:
  [
    {
      "CustID": 123456,
      "CategoryID": 5,  // PA or PotentialPA
      "TurnoverRM": 75000.50,
      "WinlossRM": -15000.00,  // Negative = loss
      "BetCount": 250,
      "ActiveDays": 20,
      "PerformanceTime": "2025-11-18",
      "CategoryName": "PA",
      ...
    },
    ...
  ]
  
  **Array**: Multiple customers in single call
end note

:Parse JSON to table;
note right
  **JSON Parsing**:
  - MySQL: JSON_TABLE function
  - Convert JSON array to rows
  - Extract each field
  - Type conversion (string → numeric)
end note

:Create temp table #ProblemAccounts;
note right
  **Temp Table Columns**:
  - CustID
  - CategoryID
  - CategoryName
  - TurnoverRM
  - WinlossRM
  - BetCount
  - ActiveDays
  - PerformanceTime
  - Other PA metrics
end note

partition "Process Each Customer" {
  repeat
    :Get next customer from temp table;
    
    :Check if customer exists in CTSCustomerClassification;
    
    if (Customer exists?) then (yes)
      :UPDATE CTSCustomerClassification;
      note right
        **Update Existing Record**:
        - Set CategoryID = PA/PotentialPA
        - Set CategoryName
        - Update TurnoverRM
        - Update WinlossRM
        - Update BetCount
        - Update ActiveDays
        - Set ProbationStartDate = NOW()
        - Set ProbationEndDate = NOW() + X days
        - Set RelevantCategoryID (for monitoring)
        - Set UpdatedDate = NOW()
        - Keep existing CTSCustID
        
        **WHERE**: CustID = current customer
      end note
    else (no)
      :INSERT INTO CTSCustomerClassification;
      note right
        **Insert New Record**:
        - Generate new CTSCustID (auto-increment)
        - Set CustID
        - Set CategoryID = PA/PotentialPA
        - Set CategoryName
        - Set TurnoverRM
        - Set WinlossRM
        - Set BetCount
        - Set ActiveDays
        - Set ProbationStartDate = NOW()
        - Set ProbationEndDate = NOW() + X days
        - Set RelevantCategoryID
        - Set InsertedDate = NOW()
        - Set UpdatedDate = NOW()
      end note
    endif

    :Set Probation Period;
    note right
      **Probation Period**:
      - Start: Current date
      - End: Start + X days (e.g., 30 days)
      - Duration depends on PA severity
      
      **PA**: 30 days
      **PotentialPA**: 15 days
      
      **Purpose**:
      - Monitor customer behavior
      - Observe betting pattern changes
      - Review at end of probation
    end note

    :Detect if Robot;
    note right
      **Robot Detection Logic**:
      Based on betting patterns and behavior
      
      **Robot Indicators**:
      1. **High Frequency**:
         - BetCount > threshold (e.g., > 500/day)
         - Very short time between bets (< 10 seconds)
         
      2. **Consistent Patterns**:
         - Same bet amounts repeatedly
         - Regular time intervals
         - Predictable behavior
         
      3. **Suspicious Activity**:
         - API-based betting (not web UI)
         - Multiple simultaneous bets
         - Instant bet placement after odds change
         
      4. **Historical Data**:
         - Previously flagged as robot
         - Similar to known robot patterns
         - Machine learning detection
      
      **Detection Methods**:
      - Pattern analysis
      - ML model scoring
      - Rule-based detection
      - Historical comparison
    end note

    if (Is Robot?) then (yes)
      :Set IsRobot = true;
      note right
        **Robot PA Customer**:
        - Different handling
        - Stricter monitoring
        - Separate logic insertion
        - Higher risk score
      end note
    else (no)
      :Set IsRobot = false;
      note right
        **Regular PA Customer**:
        - Normal PA handling
        - Standard monitoring
        - Regular logic insertion
        - Normal risk score
      end note
    endif

    :Get CTSCustID for return;
    note right
      **CTSCustID**:
      - Auto-generated (for new)
      - Retrieved (for existing)
      - Used for subsequent operations
      - Primary key in CTS system
    end note

    :Add to result set;
    note right
      **Result Record**:
      - CTSCustID
      - CustID
      - IsRobot (flag)
    end note

  repeat while (More customers?) is (yes)
  -> no;
}

:Return InsertPAProbationResult[];
note right
  **Return Type**: List<InsertPAProbationResult>
  
  **Result Structure**:
  {
    "CTSCustID": 789012,
    "CustID": 123456,
    "IsRobot": false
  }
  
  **Usage**:
  - CTSCustID for internal tracking
  - CustID for external reference
  - IsRobot for logic separation
  
  **Next Steps**:
  1. Filter by IsRobot flag
  2. Insert PA Logic (regular)
  3. Insert Robot Logic (robots)
  4. Push to MainDB
end note

:Log Execution;
note right
  **Logging**:
  - Customer count processed
  - Insert count
  - Update count
  - Robot count detected
  - Execution time
  - Any errors/warnings
end note

stop

note bottom
  **Insert/Update Logic**:
  - UPSERT pattern (INSERT or UPDATE)
  - Based on CustID existence
  - Preserves CTSCustID for existing
  - Generates new CTSCustID for new
  
  **Probation Period Management**:
  - Tracks PA customers during observation
  - Automatic end date calculation
  - Can be extended manually
  - Triggers monitoring rules
  
  **Robot Detection Integration**:
  - Automated detection during insert
  - IsRobot flag for downstream processing
  - Separate logic for robots vs regular PA
  - Enhanced monitoring for robots
  
  **Table Schema (CTSCustomerClassification)**:
  - CTSCustID (PK, auto-increment)
  - CustID (FK, indexed)
  - CategoryID (indexed)
  - CategoryName
  - TurnoverRM
  - WinlossRM
  - BetCount
  - ActiveDays
  - ProbationStartDate
  - ProbationEndDate
  - RelevantCategoryID (for monitoring)
  - IsRobot (flag)
  - InsertedDate
  - UpdatedDate
  
  **Performance Considerations**:
  - Batch insert (multiple customers)
  - JSON parsing overhead
  - Index on CustID for lookups
  - Index on CategoryID for filtering
  - Transaction wrapper for atomicity
end note

@enduml

